  "article": [
   "The winners'-bracket final is done, and it wasn't close: Rawhides dropped Bus Stop 9-4, punching a ticket straight to the grand final with the double-elimination cushion every team in this draw has been chasing since the seeds came out. The model had this coming \u2014 Rawhides was already a 79.2% favorite \u2014 but a win this size still moves the number: title odds jump to 91.1%, up 11.9 points from a week ago.",
   "Look at the box score and the match tells its own story. For Rawhides, Kevin Scheper went a perfect 3-0, while across the table Bus Stop stayed in the fight early \u2014 Wade Hargrove led the way at 2-2. It caught up with them in the end, though: Justin Anderson never got on the board, going 0-3, and the bottom of the lineup is exactly where Rawhides bracket-favorite depth is supposed to show up.",
   "The undercard carried its own gut-punch. El Farolito eliminated Pocket Fizz 9-3 to end their season, and Otoniel Jimenez went a perfect 3-0. The cruelest detail belongs to the losing side: Albert Yip and Clayton Lapointe were held scoreless, a combined 0-for-6 \u2014 on the night their season ended.",
   "3 teams remain. Bus Stop drops to the losers'-bracket final to face El Farolito \u2014 the winner of that one earns a single shot at Rawhides, and it comes with the cruelest condition in the sport: a true reset, meaning they have to beat the top seed twice in a row to take the title."
