   "body": [
    "The one-loss bracket crowns its champion. El Farolito and Bus Stop both have exactly one path left, and it runs through each other first: win this and you earn the right to chase the top seed through a true-reset grand final \u2014 beating them twice in a row, with nothing in the bank. Lose, and the season's over tonight.",
    "They've actually met once already, and it settled nothing. Back in the regular season, Bus Stop and El Farolito played to an 8-8 tie \u2014 dead level, 8 games apiece \u2014 the one result on the schedule that refused to pick a side. Now, with a season on the line and ties off the table (this is race-to-9, sudden death), somebody finally has to blink.",
    "Both arrive hot off wins that tell very different stories. El Farolito bulldozed a way here off elimination games; Bus Stop just got run off the winners'-bracket floor by the top seed and now has to prove that loss was a blip, not a trend. The model gives El Farolito 59% for the match \u2014 53% per game, effective Fargo 569 to 553 \u2014 but this bracket has made a habit of ignoring the model."
